just installed the 1.2 release version and saw that firespitter was supported in CKAN. well i was trying to build a plane and when marrying a propeller engine to my fuselage the game crashed. Any ideas?

All "tweakable" engines make KSP 1.2 go CTD. Someone just hasted to mark firespitter.dll as compatible.
excellent, thank you @Dr. Jet
Sorry, how can I solve this problem?

On 10/14/2016 at 4:48 AM, Dr. Jet said:

All "tweakable" engines make KSP 1.2 go CTD. Someone just hasted to mark firespitter.dll as compatible.

Except that I can't repro this on 1.2.2 with the current Firespitter.  So there's something else going down, probably a mod interaction.

So no, there is no need to mark it as incompatible as it is... compatible.

Well, it was october 2016 and 2 KSP patches ago.

which module manager version is supposed to be paired with the current firespitter version? im having the same problem with the adjustable rotors and tweakable engines. as soon a s they are selected from the parts list and married to your craft the game crashes. does anyone know which mods that firespitter "doesn't like"? and/or will not cooperate with?

Would help to post a log file.

And always the latest MM

14 hours ago, johnnydope said:

I have ksp v1.2.1 and firespitter 7.4.2

Current version of KSP is 1.2.2. and firespitter 7.5.1.

It is not likely that moders would provide support and waste their free time on obsolete version of mod, fixing something that is already fixed in later releases.
You might be on your own here, to download and tweak available source code, recompile and use it for yourself.

Quote

Access Violation (0xc0000005)
  in module KSP_x64.exe at 0033:3f24bc67.

This kind of error usualy comes from memory leaking - when game try to allocate more memory than it is available on system. Or in other cases, game try to access object that is either not yet created or it is created and destroyed for some reason while some piece of code is not aknowledget that and try to read or set some value to object. Can't help you much more than this, but it is starting point if you want to debug stuff for your personal usage.
